Suggestion for QA test day Testing areas:

1. Pin the Web
2. new Home screen (can only test the swapping of homescreen)
3. Music app
4. Settings
5. Task manager/Card View

(will also be re-use some of the ones that already on one and done)
--------------------------------

[pin the web] Testing basic home screen functionality
Prerequisites: 
Have Pin the Web enabled in Developer settings
Be running the new homescreen
Have multiple pages pinned and pinned page card 

1. Long press on home-screen to get into edit mode

     Home-screen will go into edit mode

2. Move pinned site icon

    Trash can icon will appear on tool bar

3. Move icon to trash

     Confirmation dialog is shown

4. Tap cancel

     Will take you back to home screen and icon will still exist


5. Long-press on home-screen to re-enter edit view

6. Move the pinned con to change location

     Can change location without problems

7. Exit home-screen editor

8. Go to Settings-> Browser privacy and "Clear browser history" and "Clear cookies and stored data"

9. Go back to home-screen, check pinned sites and pinned pages

     All pinned sites and pages still exist and can be launched correctly


------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 
 [settings] Testing basic functionality of settings
 Prerequisites:
     Have 2.5 installed
     
     Examples given for each thing to test.
Check the following:
    1. Do all toggles and sliders work?

        Example:

    a. Open Settings

    b. Scroll to area of airplane mode

    c. Toggle airplane mode on and off, make sure it's enabling and does not get stuck after repetitive flipping

    2. Do all buttons to open other areas work?

        Example:

    a. Open Settings

    b. Open the sections and make sure you can

    c. Open sub sections

    d. Make sure buttons in each section and subsection work

    3. Do all sign in areas work? (facebook, live, gmail....etc)

    Example:

    a. Open Settings

    b. Go to Firefox Accounts

    c. You can sign in and sign out as desired

    4. Is all info correct?

    Example:

    a. Open Settings

    b. Open Device info

    c. Check if version is correct, last updated is correct, etc....


----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

[music app] Does music app work correctly and find location of music on phone correctly?

    Prerequisites:

    Have the gaia nga (new gaia architecture) app and music to put on your device... just have phone fully up to date


Check the following:
    1. Can you put music on the device fine and does phone locate it correctly?

    a. Plug device into computer

    b. Enable usb storage

    c. Transfer music onto the device

    d. Disconnect device or disable usb storage

    e. Open music app

           Does it detect music correctly and load it into music app?

   2. Does the app display properly?

    a. Is anything overlapping?

    b. Does anything stand out as incorrect?

    c. Is everything in alphabetical order in the lists?

    d. In playlists, are there any spelling errors?

   3. Check the music player screen

    a. Can you go to next song?

    b. Can you go to the previous song?

    c. If shuffle is on, is the next song shuffled randomly?

    d. If song is set on repeat, does it play repeatedly?

    e. If playing an album, if you set repeat, does the album repeat after reaching the end?

     f. Can you set ratings on them correctly?

    g. Can you get back to the music player from all sections of music app using upper right hand corner? not upper left? (not verified it)

   4. Does the search work correctly?

    a. If you type a valid search for what is in the library, do the proper results display?

    b. If you type an invaild search for what is in your library does it display as so?

    c. Can you search for songs, albums and artists?


-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

[Task manger/ Card view] Does the task manger allow your to change apps, close apps and open them properly?
   





           
